The paper discusses collaborative filtering, which is a common technique used in information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG) for making recommendations. The focus on time series estimation suggests a potential connection to signal processing (cs.SI) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the use of classification and density estimation tools suggests a potential connection to natural language processing (cs.CL).
